commit.message:
format: avoid overflow when aligning an area

When the content size is larger than the wanted size for an Area,
alignment within is pointless, since the content stretches the cell.  So
don't try either, because negative values result in large overflows.

Signed-off-by: Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
*: introduce ANSI-escape code rendering

Using ANSI escapes is much more Cool(tm) than using backspace sequences.
Not only is it more efficient, it's also handled by most terminals these
days, and it works much better with UTF-8 sequences, etc.  On top of
that, one can do COLOURS, yay!  So in this commit a bunch of things are
combined on top of each other:

1. ANSI escape handling
2. colour handling, kind of messy, but sometimes works well (e.g. links)
3. table reflow handling to pick up the properties for colours and
   alignment

Signed-off-by: Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
sgml: ignore zwnj entity

This one is often misused by email marketeers(?) to get all kinds of
weird/odd behaviour.  In reality, with a monospaced font, things like
"auflage" or "deafly" won't render well when they look like "auf lage"
or "deaf ly", so it's pointless for us.  Therefore, just ignore it.

Signed-off-by: Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
HTMLControl: rework whitespace normalisation

Take a read-ahead strategy and split out leading/trailing whitespace
as explicit tokens, such that it is easier to suppress bounding
whitespace e.g. within blocks, and also not to get confused when tags
are used inbetween whitespace blocks.

Closes: https://github.com/grobian/html2text/issues/12
Closes: https://github.com/grobian/html2text/issues/26
Signed-off-by: Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
